          <updateDate>2017-02-07T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Put School Counselors Where They're Needed Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965 to direct the Department of Education to implement a demonstration project providing competitive, 4-year grants to at least 10 secondary schools that have a 4-year adjusted cohort graduation rate of 60% or lower, for the provision of additional school counselors and counselor resources.</p> <p>The bill expresses the sense of Congress that grantees should provide one additional counselor for every 250 students at risk.</p> <p>The additional school counselors must serve primarily students identified as being at risk of not graduating in four years.</p> <p>Grantees that demonstrate progress in improving their graduation rates are eligible for subsequent grants.</p>]]></text>
          <actionDate>2017-02-07</actionDate>
        </item>
